    {
      "id": "nmo5rw42py4c",
      "type": "commentNode",
      "position": {
        "x": -1020,
        "y": -160
      },
      "data": {
        "text": "https://softologyblog.wordpress.com/2018/03/09/multiple-neighborhoods-cellular-automata/\n\nEach cell uses the above neighborhood patterns to tally the live cells into 4 sum values. sum_0 is the live cell count in neighborhood 1, sum_1 is the live cell count in neighborhood 2, sum_2 is the live cell count in neighborhood 3, and sum_3 is the live cell count in neighborhood 4.\n\nThe sums are used to determine life or death for the cells by using the following formulas.\n\nIf sum_0 is between 0 and 17 then the cell dies.\nIf sum_0 is between 40 and 42 then the cell lives.\nIf sum_1 is between 10 and 13 then the cell lives.\nIf sum_2 is between 9 and 21 then the cell dies.\nIf sum_3 is between 78 and 89 then the cell dies.\nIf sum_3 is greater than 108 then the cell dies.",
        "color": "#3f3f31",
        "width": 200,
        "height": 80
      }
    },
